}

// Start the server on port 3000
app.listen(3000, () => console.log('Server started on port 3000'));
```

This program defines a route `/list/:dir(*)` that takes a directory path as a parameter and returns a webpage with a nested list of files and folders in that directory. The `getNestedList()` function is used to recursively scan the directory and construct the nested list data. The EJS template `views/list.ejs` is used to render the webpage with the nested list data.

Note: This program assumes that the directory being scanned is a local directory on the server running the Node.js application. If you want to scan a directory on a remote server or from a client-side web application, you will need to modify the program accordingly.

